Type of chicory that is milder in flavor than other chicories but with similar
			feathery leaves; pale green to white in color. Combine with arugula, watercress, or Boston or Bibb lettuces;
			serve on its own with warm bacon dressing or balsamic vinaigrette.

A good all-purpose whisk that will reach into the corners of a saucepan is key;
				you will need it to beat eggs and to keep sauces, custards, and puddings smooth during cooking. For more
				details on what to look for, see page 31.
